Deutsche Bank to Expand in Eastern Europe, FT Deutschland Says

-- B y   H o l g e r   E l f e s
-- 
2011-02-21T06:59:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/deutsche-bank-to-expand-in-eastern-europe-ft-deutschland-says.html
  Deutsche Bank AG  plans to expand its
business in Eastern Europe and may make acquisitions in the
region, the  Financial Times Deutschland  reported today, citing
Peter Tils, who heads the bank’s business there.    Germany ’s biggest lender sees growth opportunities in
Russia, Poland and  Kazakhstan , according to the newspaper.
Deutsche Bank wants to expand its business mainly through
organic growth and would consider acquisitions if they are
“really attractive,” Tils told the FTD.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Holger Elfes in Dusseldorf at 
 helfes@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
